  "prompt": "Are there alternatives to Yelp?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several alternatives to Yelp for finding and reviewing businesses:\n\n1. Google Reviews\n- Integrated with Google Maps\n- Widely used\n- Easy to access\n\n2. TripAdvisor\n- Especially good for restaurants and travel\n- User-generated reviews\n- International coverage\n\n3. Facebook Reviews\n- Large user base\n- Integrated with business pages\n- Easy to use\n\n4. OpenTable\n- Focused on restaurant reviews and reservations\n- Detailed dining information\n- User ratings and reviews\n\n5. Zomato\n- Restaurant-focused review platform\n- Global presence\n- Detailed menu and pricing information\n\n6. Foursquare\n- Location-based recommendations\n- Detailed business information\n- User tips and reviews\n\n7. Better Business Bureau (BBB)\n- Focuses on business reliability\n- Customer complaint tracking\n- Ratings and accreditation\n\n8. Nextdoor\n- Neighborhood-specific recommendations\n- Local community reviews\n- More personal approach\n\n9. Google Maps\n- Integrated reviews\n- Location information\n- Easy navigation\n\n10. Bing Places\n- Microsoft's business review platform\n- Similar to Google Reviews\n- Alternative search option\n\nEach platform has its strengths, so using multiple sources can provide comprehensive information.",
